	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I know Earthworm Jim has a little bit more stuff on the sides of the screen on the Genesis because of resolution differences.  Do any games actually rearrange the levels to the levels to fit on a smaller screen?<br /><br />The only time I remember this being used is Kirby's Super Star using 24x24 tiles to recreate Kirby's Dreamland's 16x16 tiles on the Game Boy.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


